THE 18th anniversary of St. George’s Ambulance Foundation will hold in Abuja on May 25, organisers have said. A statement by the foundation’s Vice Chairman (Board of Trustees), Adams Hamzat, said some personalities would be awarded in recognition of their leadership roles and service to humanity. They include former military President Gen. Ibrahim Babangida (Grand Patron); former President Goodluck Jonathan (Great Grand Patron), and former Vice President Atiku Abubakar (Life Patron).   Lagos keen on ensuring safe blood, blood products     NURTW leaders back MC Oluomo     We’ll sustain Buhari’s legacy, says APC…   Ooni of Ife Oba Adeyeye Ogunwusi, as royal father of the day, will receive award for his national peace initiatives and contributions during COVID-19 pandemic. Also to be awarded are National Leader of All Progressives Congress (APC) Bola Tinubu; Attorney-General and Minister of Justice Abubakar Malami; Minister of Works and Housing Babatunde Fashola, among others. The statement added that St. George’s Ambulance Foundation was the foremost humanitarian organisation that had championed emergency ambulance services in Nigeria.